OL,7,FShe argued the school's stance on
OL,8,Fprayer ` one of the five pillars of
OL,9,FIslam ` unlawfully breached her right
OL,10,Fto religious freedom and was "the kind
OL,11,Fof discrimination which makes
OL,12,Freligious minorities feel alienated
OL,13,Ffrom society".
OL,15,FThe school, founded and led by
OL,16,Fheadteacher Katharine Birbalsingh, a
OL,17,Fformer government social mobility
OL,18,Ftsar, argued its prayer policy was
OL,19,Fjustified after it faced death and
OL,20,Fbomb threats linked to religious
OL,21,Fobservance on site.
